WTI crude futures eased below $77 per barrel on Monday  pausing a recent rally as investors turned cautious ahead of key interest rate decisions from the US Federal Reserve and the European Central Bank this week. Both central banks are widely expected to lift rates again this month  though traders scaled back bets on further monetary tightening this year amid easing inflation.Meanwhile  China is expected to introduce targeted stimulus measures to support a faltering post-pandemic recovery. Elsewhere  an escalating conflict in Ukraine after Russia withdrew from a grain exports agreement also gripped commodity markets.
